Kofola is moving from Poland to the Czech Republic and is considering entering the Prague Stock Exchange.
The new headquarters should be in Ostrava.
Kofola S.A. was registered in Poland for the purpose of trading the company’s shares on the Warsaw Stock Exchange.
Our primary goal is to have a headquarters in the Czech Republic.
The steps we have taken so far within the framework of the project are mostly legal and administrative and have no actual impact on the events in the company, says Daniel Buryš, financial director of the Kofola Group.
"In connection with the move of the headquarters of the Group, shareholders are considering placing shares on the Prague Stock Exchange."
In order to enter the Prague Stock Exchange, the company is completing the prospectus of the securities, which will be submitted to the Czech National Bank for approval in the near future.
The transfer of the holding’s headquarters and related transfer of shares will be carried out in the form of a non-public transaction involving only existing shareholders.
As part of this transaction, no shares will be offered to the public or new investors.
"A possible offer of shares to new investors would take place - if the company and its shareholders decide to do so - later, either in the fourth quarter of 2015 or in the first quarter of 2016," the company said.
