In the event of a CK bankruptcy, the insurance companies must pay the claims of the clients in full.
The insurance companies should pay the claims of the clients in the event of the bankruptcy of the travel agency in full.
This was decided on Wednesday by the House of Representatives when it approved an amended amendment to the Law on Business Conditions in Tourism.
Travel agencies will be able to replace insurance against bankruptcy with a bank guarantee.
Insurance companies are not obliged to pay the claims of clients above the agreed limit.
The Ministry of Local Development insists on the adjustment, arguing for consumer protection.
Insurance companies have already threatened to end travel insurance against bankruptcy when the novel comes into effect.
The proposal has also been criticized by travel agencies.
Without insurance, they will either have to leave or go abroad.
Minister for Local Development Karla Šlechtová (for ANO) pointed out that cases where insurance companies did not pay full compensation are not euro-comform.
She pointed to this year’s ruling of the Constitutional Court, which confirmed that the client has the right to a full refund of money regardless of the insurance limit.
Insurance companies will receive sufficient information on the management of travel agencies and will be able to determine the correct limit, she stressed.
“We appreciate the effort to increase consumer protection, but it must have such a limit to be feasible,” said Deputy Chairman of TOP 09 Miroslav Kalousek.
The bank guarantee will not work, because no one will give it unlimited.
“Travel agencies will have to end their activities or move abroad,” Kalousek said.
Tomio Okamura, a member of the Presidium of the Association of Czech Travel Agencies and Agencies (SPD), disagreed with Kalouskov’s concerns on the basis of a survey among members of the CK.
“Stop showing us the lobbying of insurance companies,” he said.
The statements of the insurance companies are not considered relevant by Okamura, and there is no official written statement in this sense according to him.
They say they are investigating whether the travel agencies will make a participation, which, according to Okamura, is not a problem.
Jana Fischer (ODS), who referred to the position of the competitive Association of travel agencies of the Czech Republic, and its party colleague Petr Bendl, who spoke about stepping down the stairs to Czech travel agencies, also warned of the provision.
Travel agencies will not be able to negotiate insurance.
“Consumer protection works,” Fischer says.
The proposal to remove the controversial passage was not approved by the House.
Vojtěch Filip (KSČM) did not come up with a proposal to return the proposal to the committee due to the alleged contradiction with the Civil Code.
Philip warned about travel agencies that, according to him, could endanger consumers.
In view of the verdict of the Constitutional Court, the rapporteur of the proposal, Martina Berdychová (ANO), withdrew her proposal, which would limit the liability of insurance companies in cases where they could not know that the insurance does not cover the entire risk.
The new law will not originally propose a minimum insurance limit of four million for travel agencies that offer travel by air, and a million limit for offices that sell, for example, bus trips.
The limit will remain at 30 percent of the planned sales from travel sales.
However, the insurance limit will have to be such that it covers all customer claims in the event of bankruptcy of the travel agency.
The regulation also stipulates that travel agencies will have to newly indicate which travel agency organizes the trip.
Travel agencies will have to provide insurance companies with information about management and number of trips before concluding the contract.
The approved amendment of the Public Administration Committee also counts on further periodic information to insurance companies.
Travel agencies will have to provide them with monthly data on the number of travellers and sold trips, the total price of sold trips and the amount of advances and sales for trips and vouchers for them.
If the Ministry of Local Development finds that the travel agency has failed to comply with any of its legal obligations to the insurance undertaking, it shall, in accordance with the proposal, call on the insurance undertaking to remedy it or may prohibit it from concluding new contracts if the breach of the obligation could jeopardise the interests of customers.
The proposal also reforms the financing of mountain services.
The Ministry of Local Development will determine the amount of the subsidy to the mountain service on the basis of its application, which will be submitted until the end of April for the next year.
The application will include a report on the use of state money in the past year, a financial plan of spending and a forecast for the next two years.
According to the association, the promoter of the law, however, did not think of the situation what would happen if the insurance company terminates the CK contract.
It will not be allowed to organize the trip and customers who bought the trip before the termination of insurance will lose it according to the association.
In this case, the CK will suffer a significant loss and may fail, even if its management was in good condition.
One of the ways that travel agencies can deal with this situation is to bring a lawsuit against the state for compensation.
Another option will be to go abroad and use much softer conditions abroad and on our market then we will act only as agencies, said the vice president of the association Jan Papež.
According to him, the proposal of the novel also contains the institute of bank guarantee, but so unthinkingly that it can not be implemented in practice at all, because the bank guarantee can not sound to an unlimited amount.
